-- Lockheed CEO Hewson earned $25.2 mln in 2013
-- By Ankit Ajmera in Bangalore
-- Fri Mar 14, 2014 01:43PM EDT
-- None



March 14 (Reuters) - Weapons maker Lockheed Martin Corp <LMT.N> paid Chief Executive Marillyn Hewson $25.2 million in 2013, more than doubling her compensation in her first year in the job, according to a regulatory filing.

Hewson's base salary jumped 85 percent to about $1.4 million last year. Her stock awards increased to about $8.2 million from about $877,000, Lockheed said in a filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission on Friday. (http://r.reuters.com/zek67v) Hewson, who took the top job in January 2013, had a total package of $11.4 million in 2012, when she became chief operating officer.